🔐 2. HOW TO PREVENT MANIPULATION

This is the critical piece.

RabbitOS should NEVER trust one source.

Instead use:

🧠 Consensus Validation

Example:

truth_score = (
    scientific_sources * 0.4 +
    government_sources * 0.3 +
    community_validation * 0.1 +
    historical_accuracy * 0.2
)


---

🧾 Source Ranking

Each source gets:

reliability score

freshness score

conflict score

reputation score



---

🔍 Contradiction Detection

If:

one source conflicts heavily

data appears synthetic

source reputation drops


RabbitOS flags:

“unverified”

“conflicting evidence”

“requires human review”



